        "intro_content": "<p>The <strong>utility knife</strong> fills the gap between paring knife and chef knife, handling mid-sized tasks that feel awkward with either extreme. At 5 to 6 inches, the utility knife slices sandwiches, cuts citrus, portions chicken breasts, and handles everyday prep that does not warrant a full chef knife. XinZuo utility knives are forged in Yangjiang with the same Damascus steel as our larger <strong>kitchen knives</strong>, giving you precision and edge retention in a nimble format. Many home cooks find the utility knife becomes their most-used blade once they discover how well it handles breakfast prep, lunch assembly, and quick dinner tasks. It is the workhorse you did not know you needed.</p>",
